(412, 1, '2016-10-07 08:58:47', '2016-10-07 07:58:47', 'Hello everyone to my second post.\r\n\r\nIn this new post, in a first time I will deal about the Intelectual Property (IP) in the United Kingdom and then we will focusing more on IP rights in the creative industry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, let''s introduce a short informations on IP rights from the<a href="http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf"> World Intellectual Property Organization  (WIPO)</a> :\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #999999;">"Intellectual property refers to creations of the mind: inventions; literary and artistic works; and symbols, names and images used in commerce. Intellectual property is divided into two categories: Industrial property and Copyright"</span></p>\r\nIn this quote, the WIPO define the IP to all kind of creations of the mind, it can be a right on a car model (industrial property) as well as  music (copyright), so it can be applied at a wide range of industry.\r\n\r\nThe aim of IP rights are like any other property right : They allow creators, or owners, of patents, trademarks or copyrighted works to prevent from a exploitation of the invention by a person or a company.\r\n\r\nThis right is recognized  since 1883 and it has been established in order to give at the creator the benefit from their own work or investment in a creation\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\na qui revient les IP?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI remember the old counter strike with the wrong name of weapons\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nDefinition, from Wipo (World Intellectual Property Organization) - What is intelectual property', 'Intelectual Property rights and their importance in the creative industries', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 08:58:47', '2016-10-07 07:58:47', '', 300, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/300-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
