(398, 1, '2016-10-03 16:31:06', '2016-10-03 14:31:06', 'Hello and welcome everyone to the first post of my Blog !\r\n\r\nIn this post, I will explain you in a first time the reasons of why a Porfolio/Showreel is required to work on the creative industries, and in the second part, how make a good one to promote your profile.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLet''s start by the begining, what is a Portfolio ?\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #999999;"><img class="wp-image-393 alignleft" src="http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/download.jpg" alt="download" width="44" height="44" />"A portfolio is a living and changing collection of records that reflect your accomplishments, skills, experiences, and attributes. It highlights and showcases samples of some of your best work, along with life experiences, values and achievements." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source</span> : </span><a href="http://careercenter.cofc.edu/documents/portfolio.pdf">Career center document\r\n</a></i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis document provide us, an accurate definition of the Portfolio. Whereas a <a href="https://uk.linkedin.com/in/vincent-berthet">LinkedIn profile</a> will promote your professional experience and diploma. A Portfolio is the showcase of your work (profesional or during your free time). Moreover, if you want to work in the creative industries you must have a decent Portfolio to impress your employer !\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_354" align="alignright" width="477"]<a href="http://www.adhamdannaway.com/"><img class="wp-image-354" title="Check his Portfolio !" src="http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/portfolio.jpg" alt="portfolio" width="477" height="334" /></a> A good Portfolio Homepage, we can see his personality and skills (click)[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf I will be an employer, seeking some profiles to work in my company, I will first of all check your LinkedIn profile and then I will expect a proof of your skills, and know more about you personality and your level.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, a LinkedIn profile and a Portfolio are both complementary. They are incredible tools to promote your profile.\r\n\r\nSpeaking for myself, I believe that nowadays it is impossible to find a job in our industry without this 2 features because you will be in contest with others profiles more interesting for the employer, even if you have the best diploma.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn order to convince you of my mind, I can give you some statistics :\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #999999;"><em>"56 percent of all hiring managers are more impressed by a candidate’s online portfolio than any other personal branding tool. However, only 7 percent of job seekers have created an online portfolio." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span> <a href="http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio" target="_blank">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a></em></span>\r\n\r\nIs it not an incredible tool ? Furthermore, I can swear you that have a Portfolio will be more and more a common in few years, it is actualy only used in some fields, and I can give you an example : The creative industries.\r\n\r\nHowever, I am sure if I want to work in my country (France) and I haven''t an enought decent Portfolio or a developed network, even if there are important studios (I think especially at EA, Ubisoft,...) I am sure I will stay without any job !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo how make a decent Portfolio ?\r\n\r\nAfter studying the differents sources, I can give you a shortlist  of advices :\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Describe your old projects</li>\r\n 	<li>Update it regulary, you should give information about your work in progress</li>\r\n 	<li>Show your skills, you must impress the visitor of your website (I believe, that even if it is a complicated to do, add a showreel update showreel of your skills is the best thing you can do to enhance your profile)</li>\r\n 	<li>Promote it, however nobody will come to check your profile !</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo conclude this post, I will compare 2 Portfolio. The <a href="http://www.adhamdannaway.com/">first one </a>belongs to <a href="https://au.linkedin.com/in/adhamdannaway/">Adham Dannaway</a> it is a perfect demonstration of what should be a Portfolio for me. For the second, I will share you<a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="http://geetix.net"> a friend''s Portfolio</a>. I would like to show you that even if his website looks good, it is not a decent Portfolio to promote your profile, because there is nothing about his project or his experience  ! Could you guess he have a <a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="https://fr.linkedin.com/in/benoit-dumas">LinkedIn </a>or he had a <a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="http://web.archive.org/web/20151202174954/http://geetix.net/blog/">blog in the past</a> ?\r\n\r\nThat''s why it is important to keep his Portfolio update until he become useless and doesn''t deserve you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHope you enjoyed this post, and as I told you about the importance of a Portfolio, you will find mine in a near future !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source:  </span>\r\n\r\nPorfolio definition - from College of Charleston, <a href="http://careercenter.cofc.edu/documents/portfolio.pdf">Career center document</a>\r\n\r\nImpact of a Portfolio for job seekers - from Levo ,  <a href="http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio" target="_blank">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a>\r\n\r\nWhy a website is required - from Forbes, <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/jacquelynsmith/2013/04/26/why-every-job-seeker-should-have-a-personal-website-and-what-it-should-include/#6438b81b902e" target="_blank">Why every job seeker should have a personal website and what it should include</a>', 'What makes a good portfolio or showreel in the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-03 16:31:06', '2016-10-03 14:31:06', '', 275, 'http://localhost/blog/275-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(401, 1, '2016-10-03 16:38:22', '2016-10-03 14:38:22', 'Hello and welcome everyone to the first post of my Blog !\r\n\r\nIn this post, I will explain you in a first time the reasons of why a Porfolio/Showreel is required to work on the creative industries, and in the second part, how make a good one to promote your profile.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Let''s start by the begining, what is a Portfolio ?</strong>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #999999;"><img class="wp-image-393 alignleft" src="http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/download.jpg" alt="download" width="44" height="44" />"A portfolio is a living and changing collection of records that reflect your accomplishments, skills, experiences, and attributes. It highlights and showcases samples of some of your best work, along with life experiences, values and achievements." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source</span> : </span><a href="http://careercenter.cofc.edu/documents/portfolio.pdf">Career center document\r\n</a></i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis document provide us, an accurate definition of the Portfolio. Whereas a <a href="https://uk.linkedin.com/in/vincent-berthet">LinkedIn profile</a> will promote your professional experience and diploma. A Portfolio is the showcase of your work (profesional or during your free time). Moreover, if you want to work in the creative industries you must have a decent Portfolio to impress your employer !\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.adhamdannaway.com/" target="_blank"><img class="alignright wp-image-400" title="Check his Portfolio !" src="http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/lol.png" width="386" height="159" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf I will be an employer, seeking some profiles to work in my company, I will first of all check your LinkedIn profile and then I will expect a proof of your skills, and know more about you personality and your level.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, a LinkedIn profile and a Portfolio are both complementary. They are incredible tools to promote your profile.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSpeaking for myself, I believe that nowadays it is impossible to find a job in our industry without this 2 features because you will be in contest with others profiles more interesting for the employer, even if you have the best diploma.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn order to convince you of my mind, I can give you some statistics :\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #999999;"><em>"56 percent of all hiring managers are more impressed by a candidate’s online portfolio than any other personal branding tool. However, only 7 percent of job seekers have created an online portfolio." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span> <a href="http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio" target="_blank">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a></em></span>\r\n\r\nIs it not an incredible tool ? Furthermore, I can swear you that have a Portfolio will be more and more a common in few years, it is actualy only used in some fields, and I can give you an example : The creative industries.\r\n\r\nHowever, I am sure if I want to work in my country (France) and I haven''t an enought decent Portfolio or a developed network, even if there are important studios (I think especially at EA, Ubisoft,...) I am sure I will stay without any job !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>So how make a decent Portfolio ?</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter studying the differents sources, I can give you a shortlist  of advices :\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Describe your old projects</li>\r\n 	<li>Update it regulary, you should give information about your work in progress</li>\r\n 	<li>Show your skills, you must impress the visitor of your website (I believe, that even if it is a complicated to do, add a showreel update showreel of your skills is the best thing you can do to enhance your profile)</li>\r\n 	<li>Promote it, however nobody will come to check your profile !</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo conclude this post, I will compare 2 Portfolio. The <a href="http://www.adhamdannaway.com/">first one </a>belongs to <a href="https://au.linkedin.com/in/adhamdannaway/">Adham Dannaway</a> it is a perfect demonstration of what should be a Portfolio for me. For the second, I will share you<a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="http://geetix.net"> a friend''s Portfolio</a>. I would like to show you that even if his website looks good, it is not a decent Portfolio to promote your profile, because there is nothing about his project or his experience  ! Could you guess he have a <a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="https://fr.linkedin.com/in/benoit-dumas">LinkedIn </a>or he had a <a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="http://web.archive.org/web/20151202174954/http://geetix.net/blog/">blog in the past</a> ?\r\n\r\nThat''s why it is important to keep his Portfolio update until he become useless and doesn''t deserve you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHope you enjoyed this post, and as I told you about the importance of a Portfolio, you will find mine in a near future !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source:  </span>\r\n\r\nPorfolio definition - from College of Charleston, <a href="http://careercenter.cofc.edu/documents/portfolio.pdf">Career center document</a>\r\n\r\nImpact of a Portfolio for job seekers - from Levo ,  <a href="http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio" target="_blank">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a>\r\n\r\nWhy a website is required - from Forbes, <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/jacquelynsmith/2013/04/26/why-every-job-seeker-should-have-a-personal-website-and-what-it-should-include/#6438b81b902e" target="_blank">Why every job seeker should have a personal website and what it should include</a>', 'What makes a good portfolio or showreel in the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-03 16:38:22', '2016-10-03 14:38:22', '', 275, 'http://localhost/blog/275-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
