(448, 1, '2016-10-07 14:00:43', '2016-10-07 13:00:43', 'Hello everyone and welcome for a new post this week,\r\n\r\nThis week I will study the question of freelancing, I will deal about pros &amp; cons and give you my opinion about it. Is it a good choice of career ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_428" align="aligncenter" width="363"]<img class=" wp-image-428" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/freelance3-1.jpg" alt="A choice of career" width="363" height="284" /> A choice of career[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you may know, the freelancing in the EU is in good health, this numbers from the IPA are one more proof !</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;">"Independent professionals in the EU grew from 6.2 million in 2004 to 8.9 million in 2013.The <a href="http://www.ipa.co.uk/page/ipa-agency-census#.V_eaeCgrI2w" target="_blank">IPA''s 2014 Agency Census</a></span> <span style="color: #808080;">revealed creative roles account for 41.8% of freelance jobs for member agencies." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span> CampaignLive -</span> <a href="http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#" target="_blank">why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Statistics, from Campaign - why creative industries embracing freelance economy</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">General informations, from CreativeSkillset - <a href="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success/" target="_blank">What''s it like to work in the creative industries</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Personal view, from FastoCreate - How to be a happy and successful creative freelancer or work with one</p>', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 14:00:43', '2016-10-07 13:00:43', '', 298, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(449, 1, '2016-10-07 14:23:05', '2016-10-07 13:23:05', 'Hello everyone and welcome for a new post this week,\r\n\r\nThis week I will study the question of freelancing, I will deal about pros &amp; cons and give you my opinion about it. Is it a good choice of career ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically we can say that freelancing is being a self-employe, that provide services to multiples customers. Be his own boss and work for the most part of the time alone, his a choice of career.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_428" align="aligncenter" width="363"]<img class=" wp-image-428" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/freelance3-1.jpg" alt="A choice of career" width="363" height="284" /> A choice of career[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you may know, the freelancing in the EU is in good health, this numbers from the IPA are one more proof !</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;">"Independent professionals in the EU grew from 6.2 million in 2004 to 8.9 million in 2013.The <a href="http://www.ipa.co.uk/page/ipa-agency-census#.V_eaeCgrI2w" target="_blank">IPA''s 2014 Agency Census</a></span> <span style="color: #808080;">revealed creative roles account for 41.8% of freelance jobs for member agencies." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span> CampaignLive -</span> <a href="http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#" target="_blank">why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>This is due to many advantages of freelance :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_445" align="aligncenter" width="380"]<img class="wp-image-445" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/freelance4.jpg" alt="freelance4" width="380" height="156" /> What people believe about freelancing[/caption]\r\n\r\nOne of the most interesting advantage for freelancer, is as you work alone, you are only dependant of the customer''s order. You  can manage as you want your time during the week.Moreover, you <span style="color: #000000;">work for you because <em>you are the boss</em> here, you choose your contract with your customers.</span>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The second major advantage is that you can choose your customers, it will able you to developp your network. Furthermore due to the differentes orders you won''t make the same thing all the time !</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">With already this point of view with 2 advantages, you trust in a dream job, but there are also cons, like in all job.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Cons :</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">si bon profile &gt;preferer a des entreprise moin de frais !</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Statistics, from Campaign - why creative industries embracing freelance economy</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">General informations, from CreativeSkillset - <a href="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success/" target="_blank">What''s it like to work in the creative industries</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Personal view, from FastoCreate - How to be a happy and successful creative freelancer or work with one</p>', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 14:23:05', '2016-10-07 13:23:05', '', 298, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(450, 1, '2016-10-07 14:33:31', '2016-10-07 13:33:31', 'Hello everyone to this new post,\r\n\r\nToday I will deal about Profesionalism, especially in the creative industry. If you have already work in a company, this word won''t be strange for you, but for most of student, so I want to show you on image what is the profesionalism.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_430" align="aligncenter" width="604"]<a href="https://www.peterstark.com/quotes/professionalism-workplace/"><img class="wp-image-430" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/professionalism_1000.jpg" alt="A young businessman is adjusting his tie" width="604" height="376" /></a> This guy seems professional[/caption]\r\n\r\nPersonaly, the first word in mind when I pronounce "Professionalism" are : reliable, discipline, serving, competent. I think I will define a professional by a person who will bring what his customer desire, or even more, in the best way.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Why do I need to be professional ?</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you need to work in a important company, you can''t go to work and want to be yourself, because once you are yourself you are  naturally unprofessional.\r\nIn order to work in good terms and in the good way you need to adopt professional code, which will depends of your fields.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Identify a professional person</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_433" align="alignleft" width="300"]<a href="http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics"><img class="wp-image-433 size-full" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/ProfessionalCircles.jpg" alt="professionalcircles" width="300" height="268" /></a> Professionalism Diagram[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI have found this image on one of my source, and I think it is a good diagram to define how you can be a professional.\r\n\r\nWe can see that the professionalism is a melt beetween : behavious, skills, knowledge.\r\n\r\nObviously if you want to provide a good work to your customers you shoud have a decent skillset and knowledge, depending on your field.\r\n\r\nAlthough in my opinion I believe that behaviour is what will be differencing you as a professional and from your teammates. Because, theoretically you will have an equivalent level in technicals skills due to the fact that you are working on the same field. It will impact your communication and  your role wihin the group.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Professionalism in the creative industry</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_437" align="alignleft" width="421"]<img class="wp-image-437 " src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Robots-in-Suits.jpg" alt="robots-in-suits" width="421" height="421" /> Robots in suits[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, to be a professional you must respect the codes of your field.\r\n\r\nWhereas in buisness, restoration or even in some school you must wear a kind of uniform to work. In the creative industry, I can  say that it is more creative, there is not a defined clothing code !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever for the work providden by developper the professionalism is a really important. When you are working on a company, you probably won''t be alone on your project, that''s why communication will be very important.\r\n\r\nAlthought, there is not only the oral communication, as a developper your codes must be first of all reliable and understandable by any other developpers. They should be able to understand your codes, mainly because a computing project is updated permanently and when someone would like to help you or, even better fill your work because you left the company, in order to continue the development.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs well as you must respect a standard developping method to be understandable by anyone and communicate around your project. I believe that the third rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines and to keep update of important news in your fields.\r\n\r\nFor example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href="https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional" target="_blank">Being a creative professional</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from the context of things''s Blog - <a href="http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/" target="_blank">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\r\n\r\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href="http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics" target="_blank">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\r\n\r\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic''s Blog - <a href="http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/" target="_blank">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 14:33:31', '2016-10-07 13:33:31', '', 302, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2016-10-07 14:51:00', '2016-10-07 13:51:00', 'Hello everyone and welcome for a new post this week,\r\n\r\nThis week I will study the question of freelancing, I will deal about pros &amp; cons and give you my opinion about it. Is it a good choice of career ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBasically we can say that freelancing is being a self-employe, that provide services to multiples customers. Be his own boss and work for the most part of the time alone, his a choice of career.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_428" align="aligncenter" width="363"]<img class=" wp-image-428" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/freelance3-1.jpg" alt="A choice of career" width="363" height="284" /> A choice of career[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you may know, the freelancing in the EU is in good health, this numbers from the IPA are one more proof !</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;">"Independent professionals in the EU grew from 6.2 million in 2004 to 8.9 million in 2013.The <a href="http://www.ipa.co.uk/page/ipa-agency-census#.V_eaeCgrI2w" target="_blank">IPA''s 2014 Agency Census</a></span> <span style="color: #808080;">revealed creative roles account for 41.8% of freelance jobs for member agencies." <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span> CampaignLive -</span> <a href="http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#" target="_blank">why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>This is due to many advantages of freelance :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_445" align="aligncenter" width="380"]<img class="wp-image-445" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/freelance4.jpg" alt="freelance4" width="380" height="156" /> What people believe about freelancing[/caption]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>One of the most interesting advantage for freelancer, is as you work alone, you are only dependant of the customer''s order. You  can manage as you want your time during the week.Moreover, you <span style="color: #000000;">work for you because <em>you </em>are the boss here, you choose your contract with your customers.\r\n</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">The second major advantage is that you can choose your customers, it will able you to developp your network.</li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">Furthermore due to the differentes orders you won''t make the same thing all the time and you will permanently improve a variety of skills.</li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">As you work alone you are more pay than in a traditional company (more fees)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">With already this point of view with the dvantages, you trust in a dream job, but there are also cons, like in all job.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Cons :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">As you depend of your network''s order, you must build and maitain a decent network in order to work during all the year and get your money, there is no job security it is very important to notice that !</li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">You are not alone on the freelancer market. Remember the previous statistic, it will be a real contest between freelancer for interesting call, and there is many website to find orders (freelancer.co.uk , freelanceuk.com,  peopleperhour.com, etc)</li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">You will probably work more than a traditionnal job because as a boss you must provide papers for the administration</li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;">Lonely...</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>My own point of view :</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you have maybe guess during this article I won''t do a freelance, but it can be a good choice of career and the road to success in the creative industry.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">It is pretty interesting thing to be in charge and manage his own time and skill to respond at customer''s orders. I believe that it is a great experience, but until you have a decent network it is not a reliable situation.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">So I will recomend to start a freelance when you get the network or when you have time and don''t need a reliable situation (for your family for example).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">I believe that it can be a great experience to do few years in freelancing before to comeback on the traditional work, because it will bring you another point of view of work than you collegue, and it is always interesting to have differents experiences.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>How succeed as a freelancer  in the creative industry?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_444" align="aligncenter" width="580"]<img class="wp-image-444 size-full" src="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/freelance2.jpg" alt="freelance2" width="580" height="349" /> Road to success[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source :</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Statistics, from Campaign - why creative industries embracing freelance economy</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">General informations, from CreativeSkillset - <a href="http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success/" target="_blank">What''s it like to work in the creative industries</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Personal view, from FastoCreate - How to be a happy and successful creative freelancer or work with one</p>', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 14:51:00', '2016-10-07 13:51:00', '', 298, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
